HEADWORD: Grivet
<hw>Griv"et</hw> <pr>(gr⟦icr⟧v"⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>grivet</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A monkey of the upper
Nile and Abyssinia (<spn>Cercopithecus griseo-viridis</spn>), having the
upper parts dull green, the lower parts white, the hands, ears, and face
black. It was known to the ancient Egyptians. Called also
<altname>tota</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grize</ent>⟦br⟧
